By Ping Fei

(completed February 23,2020)

On January 23rd the city of Wuhan was sealed off, and on February 17th our community was sealed off. After that, I first participated in the group purchase of vegetables, this "group vegetable" experience ups and downs, ups and downs.

Before "Tuancai" , I had stockpiled a wave of vegetables the day before the block was sealed. On February 21, I gave a rough estimate of four days left to eat, taking into account that the group purchase would take at least two days to arrive, so from that day I began to pay attention to the various food groups in the community. Someone sent out a group purchase package, followed by a dragon, and then nothing.

Just as all the eggs can not be in one basket, so can all the hopes in one tree. So quickly find other, put the children to bed at night, pick up the phone to open the box Ma APP, just to order, hint that the delivery guy has been about 22:00 every day open the next day appointment. Check the time. 22:13. The small companion in the group says box Horse Basic 2 minutes about light, want to buy early.

On the morning of the 22nd, the group informed the group purchase of Chinese merchants "flow group" . So I started looking for APPS, APP -- beautiful -- that wouldn't be open in my neighborhood until the 24th. Meituan delivers food, but the stores are dark and closed. From the night before to the next morning, nothing. I panicked.

Finally in the Yangtze Yan election found a group purchase delivery, but to 50 from the delivery, the first day of the order, the next day delivery. Seemed to see a lifeline and wanted to grab it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Residents add a vegetable vendor's wechat account to the Baibu pavilion community on Feb. 18. After the closure of the community, ordering vegetables through the Internet and Wechat group purchase has become the choice of many owners. Photograph by China Youth Daily, my shot

But where do we have 50 people, so I want to do their own volunteers, when the "head" , to pull a group to buy food, mutual organization to help share. So I set up a "Yangtze River strict selection buy food mutual help group, " and the group's announcement read: "In special times, let's stick together as tightly as garlic, help each other in groups and work together to tide over difficulties. " Several people were pulled from the community group, pull on each other. Soon there'll be 60.

"Master" is a tough job. The merchants on the Yangtze River's strict election suggested that we do not follow the strict election of officials, but use a small program called "Peasant Gate Darts Bureau" to send faster. But this small procedure requires head certification, but also to apply to become a "Pinkerton. ". The program kicked me out of the program.

And it is not easy to select the official League strictly. Take the Dragon, we copy and paste in their own groups by the ordinal sort, this seems to be the easiest, but late docking easy to go wrong, not standard, not convenient business direct to the user. That's how I knew there was a solitaire APP.

Dragon Small Program just understand a one, two, three, the group is urging the process of buying vegetables. At this time, a lot of problems on the table, the problem of collecting fees, after the food row after the question, do not let the gathering and property contact, to help coordinate the location of the property, help the issue. Then I realized I was asking myself a lot of questions, because the group, not surprisingly, was in Florida -- There were only five people on the line before the platform closed at 18:00.

Group failure, an afternoon in the mind a bit uneasy, after all, have not found food, began to worry about the future for a period of time.

Bored, I began to collect all kinds of group buying information. Finally, a fresh fruit and vegetable shop was lit up. This time it was a real lifesaver, taking appointments and delivering food at noon the next day. But the variety is very few, basic is some green leaf vegetable, bought a few kinds, total 138 yuan. For this single vegetable, has been busy from 21 to 22.

Later, we also in the box horse and TMALL supermarket delicious food, open the APP, see what the basic choice of what, in time for 21:59 set up a shopping cart, order immediately on the hour. Finally all successful, a burst of joy, feel a period of time in the future of life and settled down.

Just about to take a break, I was pulled into a smaller shopping group by a baby mother in the community. She said that she and the customer manager of American cuisine had agreed to pull 10 people, each of whom over 300 yuan could give us an open platform group purchase once, and join the shopping cart ahead of time, the platform is only open for four minutes. I jumped in, bought flour and meat. Frozen lean meat is over 40 yuan per catty, starting at 4 catties. And four minutes of panic buying. At the moment, the joy of placing a successful order far outweighs the "pain" of rising prices.

Group purchase success, pick-up is not plain sailing. The next day, around 1:00 noon, in Meituan and Hema buy things almost at the same time, now is no contact distribution, delivery to the community on the pick-up shelves in gate, the courier left.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Residents wait to pick up vegetables ordered on the Internet outside a residential area in the baibuting community on Feb. 19. Photograph by China Youth Daily, my shot

The family went down and dragged up four large bags, two of which were from Meituan. I was amazed at how much it cost Meituan -- $138 -- to buy a box of spareribs (three) for $110. When I opened it, there was a small note inside one of the bags that said it was for another family in our unit, 1401.

The family said, two bags tightly together, only our bag attached to a shopping receipt, thought it was together, and took back.

We're on the 21st floor, and the 14th floor is right below us, so we're GONNA have to return it, rearm it, come back and sanitize it. So I said a sentence in the community grid group, "please 1401 owners and I contact the next, your Meituan take-out in my here. ".

Soon someone in the group replied, "okay. Thanks, I'll get it later. " Then I was told that 1401 had a confirmed case at home and was being quarantined.

I called the community grid operator to confirm how to deliver the package to 1401, but no one answered. Just then, the 1401 hostess told me that she had gone to the neighborhood of gate and found that the courier was not there. "Can you pick it up now? No cell phone, I'll knock on your door. ".

I was a little surprised to learn that apart from families, you can pick up a package in gate and knock on the door.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Community workers and volunteers wait for residents to pick up food at the Baibu Pavilion Community Garden on Feb. 19. Photograph by China Youth Daily, my shot

We are here to isolate the family community is never released, only released at a time which building a few units have confirmed a few suspected. Not even the floor. said it was patient confidentiality. We called the community grid guy twice and couldn't get a response, but when we went deeper he couldn't be bothered to say he wasn't on the upper-middle floor.

Under the epidemic we have no intention of patient privacy, just ask a floor, good heart knows, more do a good job of protection.

The community doesn't disclose floors, which is very unfair to everyone else in the unit. But how did the "insider" who told me that 1401 was a segregated home? It was inferred from a 1401 owner's statement in the group, then called the grid member, the grid member acquiesced, and told the insider to do a good job of protection. I mean, that's one floor up from 1401.

In the face of the 1401 female owner to pick up the goods, in the absence of contact with the grid, the proposed a compromise: she waited in the elevator on the 14th floor, I put the goods in the elevator press "14" , she picked it up when the elevator opened on the 14th floor. I put my things on the outside near the door of the elevator so that I can get them without stepping into the elevator. In this way, we also completed a "contactless distribution. ".

I called the community this afternoon, and they said there had been a complaint about a 1401 pickup. I suggest that a good unit no dead-end kill, two is to refine the isolation of the family management and services. For example, learn from other communities to prepare adequate food for isolated families, regular collection of garbage. The community worker responded: "there was a garbage collector, with a seal, and she wanted to come out. We called them and said, 'who's going to sit in front of her house and Watch? ' "

When I called the community, I asked, "is 1401 a confirmed family? "? The community did not deny this time, only that the patient was hospitalized, this is a family, close contacts, isolation at home. When I ask again, shouldn't close contacts be quarantined in quarantine? The community's getting impatient.

As I write this article, the news is still saying that Wuhan's dragnet-style investigation is aimed at four categories of personnel. I hope that the investigation of the specific work in some more detailed, more detailed.
